analysis.transcript_summary: Mike requested spray foam radio tracks for the print shop. The agent, acting as DJ Foambot, played several tracks, providing commentary and DJ sound effects. The user provided feedback, including system prompts to skip tracks. The agent initially talked too much, prompting the user to request less talking and more music. The agent acknowledged the feedback and adjusted its behavior. The conversation ended with the agent agreeing to let the tracks play without excessive commentary due to voice credit limitations.
